  <div class="clearfix main" id="main" role="main">
   <div class="container">
    <div class="row-fluid main-top" id="main-top">
     <div class="region region-main-top clearfix">
      <div class="clearfix block block-block" id="block-block-3">
       <div class="content">
        <p>
         <img alt="UC Merced - Accreditation and WASC information" src="https://accreditation.ucmerced.edu/sites/accreditation.ucmerced.edu/files/page/images/170901_wasc_banner.png" style="width: 100%;"/>
        </p>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <!-- /.region -->
    </div>
    <div class="row-fluid main-upper" id="main-upper">
     <div class="region region-main-upper clearfix">
      <div class="clearfix block block-block" id="block-block-2">
       <div class="content">
        <p>
         Welcome to UC Merced’s Accreditation website. Here you will find complete information related to UC Merced’s accreditation by the WASC Senior College and University Commission (
         <a href="https://www.wscuc.org/">
          WSCUC
         </a>
         ).
        </p>
        <p>
         In July 2018, UC Merced’s accreditation by WSCUC was reaffirmed for a 10-year period, the maximum term possible. The Commission Action Letter conveying UC Merced’s accreditation is
         <a href="https://accreditation.ucmerced.edu/sites/accreditation.ucmerced.edu/files/page/documents/cal_180720_ucm_av.pdf">
          here
         </a>
         . The letter includes both the commission’s commendations and recommendations for campus action, including preparation for an interim report due November 1, 2021.
        </p>
        <p>
         The commission’s decision was informed by
         <a href="https://accreditation.ucmerced.edu/sites/accreditation.ucmerced.edu/files/page/documents/ucm_-_team_report_av_spring_2018.pdf">
          the report of the review team
         </a>
         , that conducted the Accreditation Visit to UC Merced from February 26 to March 1, 2018, and by UC Merced’s
         <a href="https://accreditation.ucmerced.edu/sites/accreditation.ucmerced.edu/files/page/documents/uc_merced_institutional_report_for_reaffirmation_of_accreditation_july_25_2017_campus_version_0.pdf">
          Institutional Report for Reaffirmation
         </a>
         , submitted to WSCUC on July 25, 2017. A full description of the reaffirmation process, including links to relevant documents, can be found
         <a href="https://accreditation.ucmerced.edu/historical-documents/2018-reaffirmation">
          here
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         UC Merced appreciates the guidance provided by the review team and the commission in support of the campus’s continued development.
        </p>
        <p>
         Chancellor Dorothy Leland
        </p>
        <p>
         ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
        </p>
        <p>
         <strong>
          UC Merced Accreditation Liaision Officer
         </strong>
         <br/>
         <a href="mailto:lmartin@ucmerced.edu?subject=Accreditation">
          Laura E. Martin
         </a>
         <br/>
         Executive Director, Academic Senate
        </p>
        <p>
         <em>
          The University of California, Merced is accredited by the Accrediting Commission for Senior Colleges and Universities of the Western Association of Schools and Colleges, 985 Atlantic Avenue, #100, Alameda, CA, 94501, Phone: 510.748.9001.
          <a href="http://www.wascsenior.org/" target="_blank">
           http://www.wascsenior.org
          </a>
         </em>
        </p>
       </div>
      </div>
